      <p>Dolphin Centrifuge, based in Warren, Michigan, supplies purpose-built <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">disc stack centrifuge</a> systems for this application at 7,000 Gs with separation down to 0.5 microns. A quench oil centrifuge is a <strong>self-cleaning disc stack centrifuge</strong> designed for continuous purification of quench oil used in heat treatment operations. The centrifuge removes carbon, scale, rust, and metal fines from the quench oil &mdash; down to <strong>0.5 microns</strong> &mdash; using centrifugal forces exceeding <strong>7,000 Gs</strong>.</p>
